[ ] Verify and document the plan identity anchor $charter asserts the .ics UID as the anchor; confirm against current plan handling$ !3 #019f6ea6-aa84-7dc2-b7ad-b2683ab88ba0
[ ] Separate workspace config from user config; home workspace carries its own .clearhead $asymmetry today (commands/mod.rs:52, env_reader load path): projects co-locate identity+data in <root>/.clearhead, but the home workspace data lives in data_dir while its identity is read from the global user config at config_dir - separated from its data and conflated with prefs. Fix by symmetry: the home workspace gets its own config beside its data in data_dir, just-another-workspace; user config (config_dir) holds prefs and mergeable defaults only, never identity. This makes the no-inherit rule structural rather than enforced.$ !1 #019f6eaf-1f7d-7ac3-9e7b-3df500bac8c8
